<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,944,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis box="[199,330,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color pale yellow to yellow, eyes brown, face yellowish white (
<figureCitation box="[1138,1269,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 13–17</figureCitation>
). Fourth apical cell with a small brownish black spot near base (
<figureCitation box="[695,825,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,944,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis box="[199,387,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Head and thorax</emphasis>
. External features similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Luo &amp; Yang &amp; Chen, 2019" authorityName="Luo &amp; Yang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2019" box="[708,964,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Myittana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biflaka" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Benglebra">
<emphasis box="[708,739,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[754,871,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Benglebra</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[886,964,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">biflaka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[970,1059,1089,1115]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[970,1059,1089,1115]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but body slightly smaller. Crown slightly shorter than width between eyes (0.78:1); coronal suture longer than half median length of crown (0.63:1) (
<figureCitation box="[159,288,1161,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 13, 16</figureCitation>
). Pronotum as wide as head including eyes, longer than median length of crown (1.57:1) (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1423,1161,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 13, 16</figureCitation>
). Forewing elongate, considerably longer than abdomen, about 2.5 times longer than widest part (2.28:1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,944,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis box="[199,372,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with long spinous process arising from middle of ventral margin directed posteriorly and curved mesally before apex (
<figureCitation box="[525,657,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 21, 24</figureCitation>
). Valve broad anteriorly, posterior margin medially broadly produced posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[291,378,1305,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Style slightly bifid (
<figureCitation box="[634,721,1305,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus short, robust basally and laterally compressed, Cshaped in profile and curved ventrad, gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[769,943,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 20, 22–23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,944,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis box="[199,390,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Sternite VII with anterior margin nearly straight, posterior margin evenly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,1377,1404]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1339,1364]" captionTargetBox="[244,1345,503,1295]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[240,1347,522,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Female sternite VII, ventral view 25. M. (Benglebra) biflaka sp. nov.; 26. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov.; 27. M. (Benglebra) introspina (Chen &amp; Yang); 28. M. (Benglebra) ventrospina (Chen &amp; Yang). comb. nov.. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (25–28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346437/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). First and second valvulae as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Luo &amp; Yang &amp; Chen, 2019" authorityName="Luo &amp; Yang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2019" box="[503,760,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Myittana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biflaka" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Benglebra">
<emphasis box="[503,534,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[549,666,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Benglebra</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[682,760,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">biflaka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[767,857,1413,1439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[767,857,1413,1439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[871,1003,1412,1439]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1591,1616]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[240,1347,179,1563]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. First and second valvula. 29–32 M. (Benglebra) biflaka sp. nov.; 29. First valvula; 30. Detail of dorsal sculptured area of first valvula; 31. Second valvula; 32. Detail of dorsal sculptured area of second valvula; 33–36 M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov.; 33. First valvula; 34. Detail of dorsal sculptured area of first valvula; 35. Second valvula; 36. Detail of dorsal sculptured area of second valvular. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346439/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 35–36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
